<TITLE> Dhaka, Delhi in talks to iron out train issues </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 9 (bdnews24.com) -- Dhaka and New Delhi Monday discussed a string of issues to reach a final decision to connect the two neighbouring cities by rail, officials said. "A final decision is likely Tuesday," additional director general (operations) of Bangladesh Railway Qazi Asadullah told bdnews24.com. The 14 officials who came from India on the train Moitree Sunday held a meeting with Bangladesh officials at Rail Bhaban. They will stay in Dhaka until July 11 to continue discussions to iron out the unresolved issues for the launch of rail links. Asadullah said: "All matters are being discussed separately." The discussions focused on the issues including the numbers of trains, customs and immigration on the Indian part, departure stations, trial run of a train from Bangladesh and schedule for commercial runs of trains. Indian Railway Board official Shivaji Raxit said: "The meeting will resume after a recess Monday. We hope to reach a final decision tomorrow (Tuesday)." Additional secretary of the communications ministry ATKM Ismail and Indian additional home secretary AE Ahmed led their delegates to the talks. bdnews
